Figure 2:
HCT-116 cells were seeded in 96-well plates 2.0×10
. After 12 h, cells were treated with
(25, 50 and 100 μg/mL) concentrations of PREO for 24 h, removed the media and washed with PBS.
Cells were then stained with assay reagents for 30 min at ambient temperature. Cell cytotoxicity was
determined by live/dead assay. Data represent the mean±SD of three field measurements.
Figure 3:
HCT-116 cells were seeded in 6-well plates 1.0 ×10
. After 24 h, cells were treated with (25,
50 and 100 μg/mL) concentrations of PREO. After 48 hours, the medium containing essential oil was
washed off; the cells were allowed to form colonies for 12 days. Stained with 0.5 % crystal violet solu-
tion, washed once with PBS, air-dried, and counted.
